<item>
            <title>[LU-12161] Request sent has failed due to network error: [sent 1554382146/real 1554382146] </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12161</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We&apos;re getting these messages every 10 minutes or so on all of our clients:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Apr 4 13:49:06 bravo3 kernel: Lustre: 2835:0:(client.c:2116:ptlrpc_expire_one_request()) @@@ Request sent has failed due to network error: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;sent 1554382146/real 1554382146&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; req@ffff909af965f800 x1629627154208576/t0(0) o8-&amp;gt;bravo-OST0000-osc-ffff909676561800@10.21.22.51@tcp:28/4 lens 520/544 e 0 to 1 dl 1554382201 ref 1 fl Rpc:eXN/0/ffffffff rc 0/-1&lt;br/&gt;
Apr 4 13:49:06 bravo3 kernel: Lustre: 2835:0:(client.c:2116:ptlrpc_expire_one_request()) Skipped 849 previous similar messages&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What do these messages mean? Is this something to be concerned about?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for any help.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Kind regards,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Campbell&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
